description: Australians looking to undergo cosmetic surgeries might find it harder to do so under new nationwide regulations to be introduced from July 1.

title: Massive change coming to fashion-themed Palazzo Versace hotel on Gold Coast Queensland
description: Famous fashion house Versace will walk away from renewing its branding agreement with the Palazzo Versace Hotel on the Gold Coast, which is set to expire by the middle of this year.

title: Boy, 13, is rescued from claw machine at North Carolina amusement park after climbing inside
description: A 13-year-old boy became trapped in a claw machine at the Carowinds amusement park in Charlotte, North Carolina. The incident occurred when the boy climbed inside to steal a prize.

title: Daniel Andrews government warned of residential insolvencies months before Porter Davis collapse
description: The Victorian government has been accused of ignoring warnings of insolvencies in the residential construction sector months before Porter Davis collapsed.

title: Couple out of pocket $350,000 after home lost in fire is underinsured by the bank
description: A couple whose new home they had only lived in for five months burnt down in an electrical fire. Then they realised they were underinsured by $350,000 meaning they couldn't afford the rebuild.

title: Dalby Queensland police officer under investigation after 'headbutting a teenage boy'
description: An off-duty police officer is now under investigation after assaulting a teen who told him 'you're nothing without your badge'.

title: Woolworths announce recall on product sold at supermarkets in NSW and QLD
description: Urgent recall issued for deli favourite sold at supermarkets in  Queensland and NSW

title: Texas architects reveal the first look at new $60 million Uvalde school to replace Robb Elementary
description: Uvalde, Texas school board members are to  vote on approving the design of a new campus to replace Robb Elementary School almost a year after the school shooting that killed 19 kids and 2 adults.

title: Country music star Brantley Gilbert gets tossed a Bud Light during concert and SMASHES it
description: Country star Brantley Gilbert became the latest artist to protest Bud Light's partnership with with transgender activist Dylan Mulvaney by showing the beer company what he thought.

title: Bill Shorten's NDIS 'reboot' amid claims national disability insurance scheme has 'lost its way'
description: NDIS minister Bill Shorten is expected to announce the reboot in a speech to the National Press Club on Tuesday when he will admit it's been targeted by criminals.

title: Humza Yousaf 'ties himself in knots over Nicola Sturgeon'
description: Mr Yousaf said there was 'no reason' to suspend Ms Sturgeon or for her to stand down as an MSP, and he also confirmed that he would not seek to speak to her directly about the party's finances.

title: Health bosses scrap the word 'alcoholic' with staff told to say 'people who misuse alcohol' instead
description: Even the words 'men' and 'women' are too sensitive for the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence, who have deemed that NHS should stick to 'gender-neutral language'.

title: Household Cavalry rehearse into the night ahead of King's coronation
description: The Mall was chock-a-block with horses and carriages well into the early hours of this morning as military staff practised the intricate manoeuvres ahead of May 6.

title: Australia empty Covid clinics could be shut down as NSW admits no one is using them
description:
New NSW 
Treasurer Daniel Mookhey said the government was reviewing the clinics after Daily Mail Australia revealed fewer than 100 people a day used them.

title: Education Secretary Gillian Keegan backs Ofsted's one-word assessments despite headteacher suicide
description: Gillian Keegan said the ratings, ranging from 'outstanding' to 'inadequate', are 'easy for parents to navigate', despite calls from teachers for the system to be changed.

title: Stephen Lawrence's father, 81, vows to face his son's killers at parole hearing
description: Neville Lawrence, 81, confirmed that he plans to give victim impact statements at the parole hearings of the only members of the racist gang that fatally stabbed his son to be jailed.

title: HENRY DEEDES: Rishi Sunak was so clearly that goody-goody schoolboy
description: HENRY DEEDES: Everything about the Prime Minister's confident poise suggests a man who never suffered the spirit-crushing struggles of the trigonometry tutorial.

title: Was this playboy jockey who dated Pamella Bordes tortured and murdered by a British drug gang?
description: Barrie Wright, a sometime London society playboy and jockey, was held to ransom to settle a hefty debt. For three years his disappearance remained a secret to all but police, family and close friends.

title: Security is set to be 'tight' at The Derby at Epsom Downs
description: The Derby, taking place at Epsom Downs on Friday and Saturday June 2-3, attracts crowds of up top 125,000 and was a favourite of the late Queen.

title: Bruce Lehrman' returns to social media two years after Brittany Higgins broke her silence
description: The former political staffer ditched his Facebook and Instagram accounts when the rape allegations row blew up in 2021, but he is now believed to have returned to Instagram.

title: Long Island liar George Santos is running for re-election
description: George Santos announced Monday he is running for a second term in 2024 despite being outed as a pathological liar and facing probes and backlash in Long Island for fabricating his resume.

title: Home Office officials told to call asylum seekers 'customers' by civil service training programme
description: The scheme was planned in the wake of the Windrush affair, which concerned people who had been wrongly detained or deported by the Home Office. 16,000 have received the training since.

title: Police must use stop and search despite it overly affecting ethnic minorities, says Kemi Badenoch
description: Kemi Badenoch (pictured) said there 'is more work to be done to tackle disparities and build trust in our police forces' but said stop and search was a 'vital tool' and progress was being made.

title: China poses  'epoch-defining' challenge to the West, security chief warns
description: The National Cyber Security Centre head will say the UK and its allies cannot be complacent over the 'dramatic rise of China as a technology superpower'.

title: The Guardian claims Labour leader Keir Starmer is 'stuck'
description: In a withering assessment, John Harris wrote that the Labour leader is 'coasting' while Rishi Sunak is 'just about managing to look like an efficient, stable and confident leader'.

title: Queen Consort Camilla's 500 Coronation Champions are crowned
description: A panel of 20 judges met in London yesterday to decide on the final award winners from a staggering 5,000 entries.

title: Yuengling Beer trolls Bud Light with tweet celebrating their status as 'Oldest Brewery In America'
description: Pennsylvania-based beer company appeared to troll Budweiser amid the transgender Dylan Mulvaney drama, promoting a photo of their can which describes the beer as 'Traditional Lager'.

title: NADINE DORRIES: Why I didn't miss the finger-jabbing Schofield during his This Morning absence
description: NADINE DORRIES: 'What a delight it was to watch the Holly Willoughby and Alison Hammond double act on ITV's This Morning during Phillip Schofield's absence from the sofa.'

title: Merrylands stabbing: Erin Gilbert's husband breaks silence over her death inside western Sydney
description: Nic Gilbert is still living at the Merrylands home in western Sydney where his wife's final moments took place as the hunt for her killer continues.

title: I was a hacker for 30 years. These are the scariest things I saw on the dark web
description: An unethical 'black hat' turned 'white hat' hacker revealed the scariest things he saw on the dark web. This includes bad actors stealing millions of dollars to those who want to see the world burn.

title: Jesy Nelson reveals she hasn't spoken to Little Mix in two years
description: Jesy Nelson has spoken out about her devastating mental health battles during her time in Little Mix - while revealing she has not spoken to her former bandmates in two years.

title: Asda launches 'driverless' grocery deliveries in London in the largest trial of its kind in Europe
description:
The year-long trial, 
which will be the largest of its kind in Europe, covers a catchment area of 72,000 households in London. It will make use of machine learning to continually improve its AI software.

title: Two women are believed to have drowned after getting into difficulty in the Great River Ouse
description: Emergency services were called to the River Great Ouse in Kempston, Bedfordshire, on Sunday after they were contacted by a member of the public about two capsized canoes near a weir.

title: New Australian $2 coin marking Vietnam War anniversary already valued at $1,200
description: The value of a rare $2 coin commemorating Australia's involvement in the Vietnam War has skyrocketed past $1,200 since it was released a little over a week ago.
